comments: Beverley (LAC) reaches across Murray's (SAS) body and makes contact to his front that affects his SQBR.
Murray (SAS) releases from Kennard (LAC) at the end of his drive.
Williams (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Johnson (SAS) and absorbs the contact.
Williams (LAC) makes clean contact to the ball while defending Johnson (SAS) at the start of his drive.
Kennard (LAC) makes marginal contact to Johnson's (SAS) leg.
Murray (SAS) extends his leg as part of a natural shooting motion on the jump shot attempt and the contact with Williams (LAC) is marginal.
Johnson (SAS) jumps alongside of Beverley (LAC) and absorbs the contact during his driving shot attempt.
Batum (LAC) makes clean contact to the ball while defending Murray (SAS) on the perimeter.
Murray (SAS) makes contact to Batum's (LAC) arm that affects his dunk attempt.
Kennard (LAC) places a hand to the front of DeRozan (SAS) at the start of the drive but the contact marginal.
Kennard (LAC) makes marginal contact to DeRozan's (SAS) leg on his follow through after making clean contact to the ball.
Beverley (LAC) makes incidental contact with Gay's (SAS) arm during the rebound attempt.
Gay (SAS) brushes Kennard's (LAC) arm and does not affect his control of the loose ball.
Murray (SAS) makes incidental contact to Williams' (LAC) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Beverley (LAC) makes marginal contact with Gay (SAS) as he brushes his arm during the rebound.
Beverley (LAC) pushes Mills (SAS) in the back and dislodges him from his position.  After communicating with the Replay Center, it is determined that Mills is the free throw shooter.
Leonard (LAC) releases from DeRozan (SAS) during the inbound.
Leonard (LAC) extends his leg as part of a natural shooting motion on the jump shot attempt and the contact with DeRozan (SAS) is marginal.
